name: (G)I-DLE
bio: (G)I-DLE debuted on May 2, 2018 under Cube Entertainment. G)I-DLE (아이들) is a girl group from Cube Entertainment which consists of 6 members: Miyeon, Minnie, Soojin, Soyeon, Yuqi, and Shuhua. (G)I-DLE debuted with LATATA.

100% debuted on September 12, 2012 under TOP Media. 100% (백퍼센트) currently currently consists of 4 members: Rockhyun, Jonghwan, Chanyong and Hyukjin. Their leader, Minwoo, passed away due to cardiac arrest on 25th March 2018. The band debuted on September 18th 2012, under TOP Media.

name: 14U
bio: 14U debuted on July 18, 2017 under BG Entertainement. 14U is a 14 membered boy group under BG Entertainment. The group is split into two subunits - Lucky & Xplosive. Members consist of E.SOL, Luha, Gohyeon, B.S., Loudi, Eunjae, Woojoo, Doyool, Dohyuk, Hyunwoong, Hero, Rio, Sejin and Gyeongtae. They made their debut in 2017 with the song "VVV".
15& debuted on October 5, 2012 under JYP Entertainment. 15& is a kpop duo that consists of Yerin and Jimin. They debuted in 2012 under JYP Entertainment. Both of them are solo artists too.

name: 24K
bio: 24K debuted on September 6, 2012 under Choeun Entertainment. 24K (Korean: 투포케이) is a South Korean boy group formed by Choeun Entertainment in 2012. The group currently consists of seven members. They debuted on September 6, 2012 with the extended play Hurry Up.

name: 2AM
bio: 2AM debuted on July 21, 2008 under Big Hit Entertainment & JYP Entertainment. 2AM is a four member Korean group that debuted in 2008 under Big Hit Entertainment and JYP Entertainment, and formerly under CUBE Entertainment. In January 2012, they officially debuted in Japan under Sony Music Japan.

name: 2NE1
bio: 2NE1 debuted on May 6, 2009 under YG Entertainment. 2NE1 ( 투애니원) debuted in 2009, under YG Entertainment. Minzy left the band in April 2016. On November 25, 2016, YG announced that 2NE1 disbanded.

name: 2PM
bio: 2PM debuted on September 4, 2008 under JYP Entertainment. 2PM (Hangul: 투피엠) is a South Korean boy band formed by JYP Entertainment. The current members are Jun. K (formerly known as Junsu), Nichkhun, Taecyeon, Wooyoung, Junho and Chansung. Former leader Jay Park officially left the group in early 2010. The members of 2PM started when Korean musician Park Jin-young formed an eleven-member band known as One Day. Eventually the band was split into 2PM and a similar but independent group known as 2AM. 2PM debuted with the song "10 Jeom Manjeome 10 Jeom" (10점 만점에 10점, lit. "10 Points Out of 10 Points"), which showcased their acrobatic dance styles.[1] They achieved their first number 1 single with "Again & Again". Both singles featured on their first studio album, The First Album 1:59PM, released in 2009. The band went on to release another Korean album, known as Hands Up, in 2011. They made their Japanese debut later that year with Republic of 2PM. After more than a year, the group returned in 2013 with their third studio album Grown. In early September 2014, 2PM returned with their fourth studio album Go Crazy. On 15 June 2015, 2PM made a comeback with their fifth studio album No.5. After much anticipation 2PM returned on 13 September 2016 with their sixth studio album Gentlemen's Game.

name: 4MEN
bio: 4MEN debuted on February 1, 1998 under MAJOR9. 4Men is a South Korean R&B group under MAJOR9. They initially had 4 members but is currently promoting as a duo.

name: 4Minute
bio: 4Minute debuted on June 10, 2009 under Cube Entertainment. 4Minute (Korean: 포미닛) was a five-member South Korean girl group formed in 2009 by Cube Entertainment with music singles and albums released primarily in South Korea and Japan. The members of the group were Nam Ji-hyun, Heo Ga-yoon, Jeon Ji-yoon, Kim Hyun-a, and Kwon So-hyun.The group debuted in June 2009 with its first single, "Hot Issue", and in December 2010, it released its first Japanese album, Diamond. In 2011, the group released its first Korean full-length album, 4Minutes Left. The group disbanded the 15th of June in 2016, as Cube Entertainment announced that Jihyun, Jiyoon, Gayoon and Sohyun didn't renew their contracts.

name: 4TEN
bio: 4TEN debuted on August 26, 2014 under Jungle Entertainment. 4TEN (포텐), previously known as POTEN, is a 3-member South Korean girl group under Jungle Entertainment. The group consists of Hyeji, HeeO and Hyejin. They made their debut on August 26th, 2014.

name: 5urprise
bio: 5urprise debuted on August 27, 2013 under Fantagio. 5urprise was launched by talent agency Fantagio in August 2013. The group consists of five members: Seo Kang-joon, Gong Myung, Yoo Il, Kang Tae-oh and Lee Tae-hwan. They were selected through Fantagio's "Actor′s League," a program for discovering aspiring actors, and were trained for two years before making their debut.

name: 8Eight
bio: 8Eight debuted on August 27, 2007 under Big Hit Entertainment. 8Eight is a co-ed group formed by Big Hit Entertainment with members Lee Hyun, Joohee and BaekChan. The group officially disbanded in 2014.

name: A-Jax
bio: A-Jax debuted on June 1, 2012 under DSP Media. A-Jax (Hangul: 에이젝스) is a 5 member boygroup from DSP Entertainment. The current member lineup consists of Dowoon (formerly Hyeongkon), Yunyoung, Seungjin, Seungyub, and Jonghee.

name: A.C.E
bio: A.C.E debuted on May 23, 2017 under Adventure Calling Emotions. A.C.E (에이스) is a Korean boy group consisting of 5 members: Donghun, Jun, Wow, Jason and Chan. They are under Beat Interactive and debuted on May 23, 2017. A.C.E stands for Adventure Calling Emotions.

name: A.Cian
bio: A.Cian debuted on October 10, 2012 under Wings Entertainment. A.Cian (Hangul: 에이션) is a Korean Boygroup under Wings Entertainment. The members are Jungsang, Hyukjin, Jin.O and Sanghyeon.

name: A.KOR
bio: A.KOR debuted on September 5, 2014 under STL Entertainment. A.KOR (Hangul: 에이코어) is a Korean Girlgroup that consists of 3 members: Jiyoung, Kemy and Minju. They made their debut on September 5th, 2014 under Doo Republic Entertainment.

name: A.Z.M
bio: A.Z.M debuted on March 2, 2018 under INNO-K Entertainment. A.Z.M (에이지엠), also known as A To Z Music, is a South Korean girl group under INNO-K Entertainment. They debuted on March 2, 2018 with the song E.D.G.E.

name: A'ST1
bio: . A'ST1 is a boy group formed by Daesung Entertainment. Members include Azuma Tomoki, Park Jung Jin, Ding Hai Ming, Byun Jang Moon, Sung In Kyu and Lim Han Byul. The group disbanded in 2009.

name: AboutU
bio: AboutU debuted on February 24, 2018 under AMP Music. AboutU (어바우츄) is a South Korean band under AMP Music. The members are Doyoon, Victor, Changmo and Lee Soo.

name: After School
kor_name: 애프터스쿨 アフタースクール
bio: After School debuted on January 15, 2009 under Pledis Entertainment. After School (Hangul: 애프터스쿨, Katakana: アフタースクール, also stylized as AFTERSCHOOL) is a South Korean girl group formed by Pledis Entertainment with an admissions and graduation concept. After School officially debuted in January 2009 with "AH!". They then released "Diva" and "Because of You" later in the year, which were instant hits and became a commercial and critical success for the group. Follow-up singles "Bang!", "Shampoo" and "Flashback" further consolidated their domestic and international popularity. Their latest release is the maxi-single First Love, with its pole-dancing routine garnering praise from Billboard, complementing the group as the "top performers in K-Pop"

name: AiRiSu
bio: AiRiSu debuted on July 25, 2018 under Jang Entertainment. AiRiSu (아이리수) is a South Korean girl group under Jang Entertainment.

name: Akdong Musician
bio: Akdong Musician debuted on December 12, 2012 under YG Entertainment. Akdong Musician is a South Korean duo who participated on K-pop Star 2 in 2012 and debuted under YG Entertainment in 2014 after they won the second installment of the K-pop Star series. The duo consists of siblings Lee Chan-hyuk and Lee Su-hyun.

name: All-Star
bio: All-Star debuted on August 1, 2015 under Independent. All-Star (Hangul: 올스타) is a male duo that is managed independently. The members are Noah and Joonhyeon. They debuted with the song"Sugar" on August 1st, 2015.

name: AlphaBat
bio: AlphaBat debuted on November 14, 2013 under W Entertainment. Alpha:Bat (알파벳) is a 5 member group from W Entertainment. They debuted with AB City in 2013. The current lineup consists of B:eta, E:pilson, G:amma, K:appa and L:amda.

name: AOA
bio: AOA debuted on August 9, 2012 under FNC Entertainment. AOA (Hangul: 에이오에이; an acronym for Ace of Angels) is a South Korean idol girl group signed under FNC Entertainment. Initially, AOA debuted as an eight-member girlband that consisted of Choa, Jimin, Yuna, Youkyung, Chanmi, Hyejeong, Seol- hyun, and Mina. Currently, AOA is promoting as a six-member idol girl group following Choa's departure, and Youkyung, who was only a part of AOA Black. The group officially debuted by having their debut music stage on August 9, 2012, on M Countdown.

name: Apink
bio: Apink debuted on April 19, 2011 under Plan A Entertainment. Apink (Korean: 에이핑크, Japanese: エーピンク; also written as A Pink) is a South Korean girl group formed by Plan A Entertainment. in 2011. The group consists of Park Chorong, Yoon Bomi, Jung Eunji, Son Naeun, Kim Namjoo and Oh Hayoung. Hong Yookyung left the group in April 2013 to focus on her studies. Apink made their official debut on April 19, 2011, with the mini album, Seven Springs of Apink, along with the title track "I Don't Know". In October 2014, Apink released their first Japanese single, "NoNoNo".The group has won awards at shows such as the 26th Golden Disc Awards, 21st Seoul Music Awards and 13th Mnet Asian Music Awards. Their first music program win was on M Countdown on January 5, 2012, for "My My" from their second mini-album Snow Pink. Apink has won more than 30 music awards and 32 music program awards. To date Apink has released six Korean mini- albums, three Korean studio albums and three Japanese studio albums.

name: Apple.B
bio: Apple.B debuted on August 1, 2017 under GH Entertainment. APPLE.B (애플비) is a Korean pop girl group under GH Entertainment.

name: April
bio: April debuted on August 24, 2015 under DSP Entertainment. April also stylized as APRIL is a South Korean girl group formed by DSP Media in 2015. They debuted on August 24, 2015, with the mini-album Dreaming and its title track "Dream Candy". The group is currently consisting of six members: Chaekyung, Chaewon, Naeun, Yena, Rachel and Jinsol.

name: Astro
bio: Astro debuted on February 23, 2016 under Fantagio Entertainment. Astro is a South Korean boy band formed by Fantagio. The group is composed of six members: MJ, JinJin, Eunwoo, Moon Bin, Rocky, and Sanha. They debuted on February 23, 2016 with the song Hide & Seek off of their debut mini album Spring Up, which peaked at #6 on the Billboard World Albums Chart in the United States, as well as #4 on Gaon Music Chart. On December 21, 2016 Billboard named Astro one of the best new K-Pop groups of 2016.

name: ATEEZ
bio: ATEEZ debuted on October 24, 2018 under KQ Entertainment. ATEEZ (에이티즈) formerly known as KQ Fellaz is a South Korean boy group under KQ Entertainment.

name: B.A.P
bio: B.A.P debuted on January 26, 2012 under TS Entertainment. B.A.P (비에이피) currently consists of 5 members: Himchan, Daehyun, Youngjae, Jongup and Zelo. The group debuted on January 26th, 2012 under TS Entertainment. Leader Bang Yongguk departed from the group after his contract expired in 2018.

name: B1A4
bio: B1A4 debuted on April 23, 2011 under WM Entertainment. B1A4 ( 비원에이포) consist of 5 members: Jinyoung, CNU, Sandeul, Baro and Gongchan. The band debuted on April 23, 2011 under WM Entertainment. Starting 2015 they use LOEN Entertainment to distribute their physical albums. In 2018, Baro and Jinyoung did not renew their contracts in WM Entertainment and officially left B1A4.

name: B2ST (BEAST)
bio: B2ST (BEAST) debuted on April 16, 2009 under Cube Entertainment. BEAST was the first boy group under Cube Entertainment. The members were Dujun, Yoseob, Junhyung, Gikwang, Hyunseung and Dongwoon. Five of the members left the company in 2016 and re-debuted under the name Highlight while Hyunseung started a solo career.

name: Baby Boo
bio: Baby Boo debuted on June 5, 2015 under RIAK Entertainment. Baby Boo was a girl group under RIAK Entertainment with members Shine, Daon and Dabin.

name: BABY V.O.X
bio: BABY V.O.X debuted on July 10, 1997 under DR Music. Baby V.O.X was a five-member girl group that enjoyed huge success not only in Korea but overseas as well. The most successful line-up was composed of Cha Yumi, Jang HyunJung, Lee HeeJin, Kim Heejung and Kan Miyoun.

name: Batu
bio: Batu debuted on February 7, 2018 under RVA. Batu is a South Korean band under RVA. They debuted on February 7, 2018 with the digital single Spring Fever (춘곤증).

bio: Be.A debuted on January 7, 2014 under Chrome Entertainment. Be.A (Hangul: 비에이, shortened from Be. A rtist or Be an Artist; formerly known as K-Much) is a South Korean boy band formed under Chrome Entertainment in 2014. They debuted on 7 January 2014 as K-Much with the release of their first mini album Beyond the Ocean. The group currently consists of five members: Hong-gyu, Yeong-kyun, Milly, Ato and BomB.

name: Beatwin
bio: Beatwin debuted on January 6, 2014 under Elen Entertainment. Beatwin (비트윈) is a 3-member boy group from Elen Entertainment (formerly Heavenly Stars Entertainment). They debuted on January 6th, 2014 with members Sunhyeok, Youngjo, Sangyu, Jungha, Yoonhu, and Seongho. Their debut single was "She's My Girl." Member Sangyu left the group in 2015 to pursue solo activities.

name: Berry Good
bio: Berry Good debuted on May 21, 2014 under Asia Bridge Entertainment. Berry Good (Hangul: 베리굿) is a South Korean girl group formed by Asia Bridge Entertainment in 2014. The groups current line-up consists of Taeha, Johyun, Seoyul, Daye, Sehyung and Gowoon.

name: Bestie
bio: Bestie debuted on July 11, 2013 under YNB Entertainment. BESTie (베스티) was a 4-member group under YNB Entertainment. The members were Uji, Hyeyeon, Haeryung and Dahye.

bio: BgA debuted on May 13, 2016 under Wong Fu Production. Boys generally Asian, also known as BgA, is a parody K-pop group formed in 2016 by YouTuber Ryan Higa, also known as nigahiga, which is his Youtube name

G Dragon : Leader, Main Rapper, Vocalist TOP :Lead Rapper, Visual Taeyang : Main Vocalist, Main Dancer Daesung : Lead Vocalist Seungri : Lead Dancer, Vocalist, Maknae

bio: Bigflo debuted on June 19, 2014 under H.O Entertainment. Bigflo (Hangul: 빅플로) currently consists of 5 members: Euijin, Sungmin, Ron, Lex and Hightop. The band debuted on 23rd June, 2014 under Hyeyoom Entertainment.

name: Bigstar
bio: Bigstar debuted on July 12, 2012 under Brave Entertainment. Bigstar (빅스타) is a 4 member boy group from Brave Entertainment. They debuted in 2012 with the song "Hotboy." The member lineup currently consists of Feeldog, Raehwan, Seunghak, and Jude. Member Barom left the group after enlisting.

name: Black6ix
bio: Black6ix debuted on April 7, 2017 under Black Hole Entertainment. BLACK6IX (블랙식스) is a 6 member boy group under Black Hole Entertainment. They debuted in April of 2016 with the song "Please." The current member line-up consists of Yey, Taeyoung, The King, Jongwoon, Ziki, and Yongseok.

name: BLACKPINK
bio: BLACKPINK debuted on August 8, 2016 under YG Entertainment. Black Pink, stylized as BLACKPINK or BLΛƆKPIИK, is a South Korean girl group formed by YG Entertainment and the first girl group that debuted under the entertainment agency in seven years after 2NE1

name: BLANC7
bio: BLANC7 debuted on March 7, 2017 under Jackpot Entertainment. BlANC7 (블랑세븐) consists of 7 members. They debuted on March 3rd, 2017, with the song “YEAH”, under Jackpot Entertainment.

name: BLK
bio: BLK debuted on November 28, 2017 under BYKING Entertainment.

name: Block B
bio: Block B debuted on April 13, 2011 under Seven Seasons. Block B is a South Korean boy group created by Cho PD in 2011. The group consists of seven members, Taeil, B-Bomb, Jaehyo, U-Kwon, Park Kyung, Zico and P.O. In 2018, Zico left Seven Seasons, leaving Block B as a 6-member group.

name: Bolbbalgan4
bio: Bolbbalgan4 debuted on April 20, 2016 under Shofar Music. Bolbbalgan4 is a duo consisting of Ahn Ji-young and Woo Ji-yoon, who both first appeared in Superstar K6 in 2014. They debuted on April 22, 2016, with the single "Fight Day" from the mini-album Red Ickle

name: Bonusbaby
bio: . Bonus Baby (보너스베이비) consists of 6 members. The band debuted on January 01, 2017 under Maroo Entertainment

name: Boyfriend
bio: Boyfriend debuted on May 26, 2011 under Starship Entertainment. Boyfriend (보이프렌드) is a Kpop band that consists of 6 members: Donghyun, Hyunseong, Jeongmin, Youngmin, Kwangmin and Minwoo. The band debuted on May 26, 2011, under Starship Entertainment.

name: Boys Republic
bio: Boys Republic debuted on June 5, 2013 under Universal Music Group. Boys' Republic (소년공화국) consists of 5 members: Onejunn, Sunwoo, Sungjun, Minsu, and Suwoong. The group debuted on June 05, 2013, under Universal Music Group. In 2018, the group announced an Indefinite Hiatus.

name: Brave Girls
bio: Brave Girls debuted on March 2, 2011 under Brave Entertainment. Brave Girls (Hangul: 브레이브걸스; RR: Beureibeu Geolseu) is a South Korean girl group formed by producer Brave Brothers of Brave Entertainment in 2011. They debuted as a five-member group with the single album The Difference on April 7, 2011, promoting the songs "Do You Know (아나요)" and "So Sexy". On July 29, they made their comeback with "Easily", from their mini album Back to da Future. The group promoted a remix version of Easily on August 13 and released it on August 26. They made also an appearance in the movie Mr. Idol.

name: Brown Eyed Girls
bio: Brown Eyed Girls debuted on March 2, 2006 under Mystic Entertainment. Brown Eyed Girls (브라운 아이드 걸스) contains of 4 members: JeA, Miryo, Narsha, and Ga-In. The group debuted on March 2, 2006, under Mystic Entertainment.

name: BSS
bio: BSS debuted on March 21, 2018 under Pledis Entertainment. BSS is a three-member sub-unit of the South Korean boy group SEVENTEEN.

name: BTOB
bio: BTOB debuted on March 21, 2012 under Cube Entertainment. BTOB (Korean: 비투비) is a seven member boy group under Cube Entertainment, they made their debut on March 21st, 2012 with their first digital single 비밀 (Insane) and made their debut stage on March 22nd, 2012 with their title tracks Insane and Imagine on Mnet's M! Countdown.

name: BTS
bio: BTS debuted on June 13, 2013 under Big Hit Entertainment. BTS (방탄소년단; Bangtan Sonyeondan), also known as the Bangtan Boys, is a seven-member South Korean boy band formed by Big Hit Entertainment. They debuted on June 12, 2013 with the song "No More Dream" from their first album 2 Cool 4 Skool.

name: Bulldok
bio: . Bulldok (불독) currently consists of Genie and Kimi. The band debuted on October 20, 2016, under Kconic Music. On May 18, 2017, it was announced Hyung Eun left the band. On Sept 4, 2017, it was announced Sora left the band. On October 22, 2017, it was announced that Say left the band. On January 18, 2018, it was announced that Bulldok disbanded.

name: Busters
bio: Busters debuted on November 27, 2017 under JTG Entertainment.

name: C-CLOWN
bio: C-CLOWN debuted on July 19, 2012 under Yedang Entertainment.

name: Celeb Five
bio: Celeb Five debuted on January 24, 2018 under VIVO TV. Celeb Five (Hangul: 셀럽파이브) is a Korean Girlgroup comprised of comediennes Kim Shinyoung, Shin Bongsun, An Youngmi and Song Eunyi.

name: Cherry Bullet
bio: . Cherry Bullet (Korean: 체리블렛; Japanese: チェリーバレット) is a 10 member girl group under FNC Entertainment. They're set to debut in early 2019.

name: ChoColat
bio: ChoColat debuted on August 2, 2011 under Paramount Music Entertainment. Chocolat (Hangul: 쇼콜라, Syokolla), commonly stylized as ChoColat, was a South Korean girl group created by Paramount Music in 2011. The group's name stems from the idea that each member is reminiscent of a different type of chocolate. The name of the group was initially going to be "Chocolate", but there was already a group with that name, so Paramount Music decided to use the French word chocolat instead.[1] The group consists of mixed race members. The group became inactive in 2013. Melanie confirmed in an interview that the group members' contracts had concluded in February 2017 and the group had disbanded.

name: Clazziquai Project
bio: . Clazziquai Project is a Korean group that originally started as an experimental project of DJ Clazzi (a.k.a Gim Seong Hun) in 2001. Also known as CLAZZIQUAI PROJECT, Clazziquai or CLAZZIQUAI, and CZQ. His music, similar to Shibuya-Kei's, is a fusion of different genres, but above all covers electronic, house, acid jazz, and groove.

name: CLC
bio: CLC debuted on March 19, 2015 under Cube Entertainment. CLC (Hangul: 씨엘씨) is a South Korean Girlgroup formed by Cube Entertainment in 2015. The group currently consists of seven members: Oh Seung-hee, Choi Yu-jin, Chang Seung-yeon, Sorn, Jang Ye-eun, Elkie and Kwon Eun-bin.

name: Click-B
bio: . Click-B (클릭비) is a South Korean boy group and band formed in August 1999 under DSP Media. Click-B started out as a band combining rock and dance beats in their music.

name: CNBLUE
bio: CNBLUE debuted on August 19, 2009 under FNC Entertainment. CNBLUE also known as Code Name Blue, is a South Korean rock band formed in Seoul in 2009. The band consists of Jung Yong- hwa (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), Lee Jong- hyun (lead guitar, vocals), Lee Jung-shin (bass guitar, vocals) and Kang Min-hyuk (drums, vocals). CN was short for Code Name and BLUE is an abbreviation of the members' individual images. 'Burning' represents Lee Jong-hyun, 'Lovely' represents Kang Min-hyuk, 'Untouchable' represents Lee Jung Shin, and 'Emotional' represents Jung Yong-hwa.

name: CocoSori
bio: CocoSori debuted on January 5, 2016 under Mole Entertainment. Cocosori is a duo group under Mole Entertainment consiting of Coco Lee and Kim Sori. Coco is a former member of Baldy and has a youtube channel called Rilacoco. Sori is a former member of Real Girls Project. They both are soloists.

name: Cosmic Girls
bio: Cosmic Girls debuted on February 25, 2016 under Starship Entertainment. Cosmic Girls 우주소녀 (WJSN) is a Korean-Chinese collaboration project by Starship Entertainment and Yuehua Entertainment that was formed in December 2015. The agencies have dropped teasers about the girls through "units", constitutes for the first (English) letter of each syllables of the word 우주소녀 (wu-ju-so-nyeo), each week starting December 10. The first unit, called Wonder, was revealed, consisting of members Cheng Xiao, Bona and Dayoung. The next week after, the second unit, called the Joy that which has members Yeoreum, Eunseo and Xuan Yi. Then the third unit, Sweet, was posted on December 24 with members SeolA, Exy and Soobin. And on the final day of the month, the Natural unit was dropped as it unveils the final members, Mei Qi, Luda and Dawon, of the 12 member group Cosmic Girls 우주소녀 (WJSN). Later, the agencies and the group have decided to add a 13th member Yeonjung. Later Starship Entertainment said she has finished all activities with girl group I.O.I and will be joining Cosmic Girls

name: Crayon Pop
bio: Crayon Pop debuted on July 19, 2012 under Chrome Entertainment. Crayon Pop (Hangul: 크레용팝) is a South Korean girl group formed under Chrome Entertainment in 2012. The group consists of four members: Geummi, Ellin, Choa, and Way. Their fifth member, Soyul left the group in 2017. Crayon Pop officially debuted in July 2012 with their performance of "Saturday Night" on Mnet's M! Countdown. Their first EP was not a commercial success, and when their song "Dancing Queen" was released in October, the group had few opportunities to promote on music shows. Instead they held guerrilla performances on the streets of Seoul, which helped increase their fanbase. On May 31, 2017, it was announced that Soyul left Crayon Pop.

name: Cross Gene
bio: Cross Gene debuted on June 14, 2012 under Amuse Korea. Cross Gene (크로스진) is a 5 member boy group under Amuse Korea. They debuted June 14th, 2012 with the song "La-Di-Da-Di". The current member lineup consists of Shin, Takuya, Seyoung, Sangmin, and Yongseok. Member Casper left in early September of 2017 due to a conflict of interest.

name: D-CRUNCH
bio: D-CRUNCH debuted on August 6, 2018 under ALL-S Entertainment. D-Crunch also known as Diamond Crunch a korean boy group that debuted on August 6, 2018 consisting of 9 members O.V, Hyunwook, Hyunho, Hyunoh, Hyunwoo, Minhyuk, Chanyoung, Dylan and Jeongseung. They are under ALL-S Entertainment.

name: D.I.P
bio: D.I.P debuted on November 9, 2016 under Inter BD Entertainment. D.I.P - Diplomat (디아이피) is a 6 member boy group under Inter BD Entertainment. They debuted in 2016 with the song "Fizz." The current member lineup consists of Hyeonseong, Seungho, Soomin, B.Nish, Uhyeong, and Taeha.

name: Dal Shabet
bio: Dal Shabet debuted on January 3, 2011 under Happy Face Entertainment.. Dal★Shabet (달샤벳) currently consists of 4 members: Serri, Ayoung, Woohee and Subin. The group debuted on January 3, 2011, with “Supa Dupa Diva”, under Happy Face Entertainment

name: Davichi
bio: Davichi debuted on February 4, 2008 under MMO Entertainment. Davichi (다비치) is a South Korean pop duo under MMO Entertainment. The duo consists of Haeri and Minkyung. They officially debuted on February 4, 2008.

name: Day6
bio: Day6 debuted on September 7, 2015 under JYP Entertainment. Day6 is a South Korean rock band formed by JYP Entertainment. The band's current line-up consists of Jae, Sungjin, Young K, Wonpil, and Dowoon. The band debuted with the release of their first EP, The Day on September 7, 2015.

name: DIA
bio: DIA debuted on September 14, 2015 under MBK. DIA (/ˈdaɪə/; Korean: 다이아; shortened from DIAMOND and backronym for Do It Amazing) is a South Korean girl group formed by MBK Entertainment in 2015. They made their debut as a seven-member group in September 2015 with their full album Do It Amazing and its title track "Somehow". The group currently consists of eight members: Eunice, Jueun, Huihyeon, Jenny, Yebin, Chaeyeon, Eunchae and Somyi.

name: Dreamcatcher
bio: Dreamcatcher debuted on January 13, 2017 under Happy Face Entertainment. Originally formed under the name Minx, Happy Face entertainment announced they'd rebrand the group as Dreamcatcher in late 2016. Two new members were added to the lineup, Handong, and Gahyeon.

name: Dreamnote
bio: . Dreamnote (드림노트), an 8-member girl group under iMe Entertainment, currently consists of members: Sumin, Eunjo, Habin, Lara, Hanbyeol, Miso, Youi and Boni. Dreamnote is expected to debut in November, 2018. They were meant to be a nine-member group until former member Jinsol dropped out in June of this year.

name: Drug Restaurant
bio: Drug Restaurant debuted on May 27, 2015 under C9 Entertainment. Drug Restaurant (드럭 레스토랑), previously known as Jung Joon Young Band, is a South Korean rock band under C9 Entertainment. The band consists of Jung Joon Young, Dammit, Seokwon and Drok. Q. The band released their debut album on May 27, 2015. They changed their name to Drug Restaurant in 2016, because they wanted to go with a name that focuses on the band as a whole.

name: Dynamic Duo
bio: Dynamic Duo debuted on May 17, 2004 under Amoeba Culture. Korean hip hop duo with members Choiza and Gaeko. They became popular with their 2004 debut album, Taxi Driver, which became the best-selling Korean hip hop album ever.

name: Elris
bio: Elris debuted on June 1, 2017 under Hunus Entertainment. ELRIS (엘리스) consists of 5 members (Bella, Hyesung, Yukyung, Sohee, and Karin) The group debuted on June 1, 2017 under Hunus Entertainment

name: Empire Girls
bio: . Empire Girls (tentative name) is what the female trainees under Star Empire are called. The current members are Dawon, Yunji, Sihyeon, Jiyeon, Hyokyeong and Jueun.

name: Epik High
bio: Epik High debuted on October 21, 2003 under YG Entertainment.

name: EXID
bio: EXID debuted on February 16, 2012 under Banana Culture Entertainment. EXID, is a South Korean girl group formed in 2012. The group consists of five members: Solji, LE, Hani, Hyelin and Jeonghwa.

name: EXO
bio: EXO debuted on April 8, 2012 under S.M. Entertainment. The group initially debuted with twelve members separated into two subgroups, EXO-K (Suho, Baekhyun, Chanyeol, D.O., Kai, and Sehun) and EXO-M (Xiumin, Lay, Chen and former members Kris, Luhan and Tao), performing music in Korean and Mandarin respectively. They have been active as a single group since 2014 while continuing to release and perform music in multiple languages. The group became nine after the departures of Kris, Luhan and Tao. Since 2016, three members, Chen, Baekhyun and Xiumin, have also been active as a subunit named EXO-CBX, incorporating the initials of each member's stage names. Their Chinese member Lay has released two solo chinese albums in 2016 and 2017.

name: Exo-CBX
bio: Exo-CBX debuted on October 31, 2016 under SM entertaiment. Exo-CBX (Hangul: 엑소-첸백시; stylized as EXO-CBX, also known as CBX or ChenBaekXi) is the first official sub-unit of South Korean boy group Exo. Formed by S.M. Entertainment in 2016, the group is composed of three Exo members: Chen, Baekhyun, and Xiumin.

name: F.CUZ
bio: F.CUZ debuted on January 8, 2010 under Independent group. F.CUZ is a Korean group with five members: Jin On, Kan, Ye Jun, Rae Hyun, and Dae Gun. In November of 2016, the group didn't renew their contract with their previous agency, making them an independent group.

name: f(x)
bio: f(x) debuted on August 24, 2009 under S.M. Entertainment. F(x) (에프엑스) consists of 4 members: Victoria, Amber, Luna and Krystal. In August 2015, Sulli officially left the group to concentrate on her acting. F(x) debuted on September 1, 2009 under SM Entertainment

name: FANATICS
bio: . Fanatics (Hangul: 파나틱스) is an upcoming Korean Girlgroup from FENT - FASCINO Entertainment. The Sub-Unit Flavor will debut before the Official Group and it´s members consist of Doah, Chiayi and Yoonhye.

name: Favorite
bio: Favorite debuted on July 6, 2017 under ASTORY Entertainment. Favorite (페이버릿) is a 6 member girl group consisting of Gaeul, Saebom, Seoyeon, Sukyung, Junghee, and Ahra.

name: Fiestar
bio: Fiestar debuted on August 31, 2012 under LOEN Entertainment. Fiestar (Korean: 피에스타) is a South Korean girl group formed by LOEN Entertainment in 2012. The group originally composed of six members: Jei, Cao Lu, Linzy, Hyemi, Yezi and Cheska. Member Cheska officially departed from the group in March 2014. The group released their debut single, Vista on August 31, 2012.

name: Fin. K. L
bio: Fin. K. L debuted on May 25, 1998 under DSP Media. Fin. K. L was a famous girl group that debuted in 1998. Their name stands for Fin Killing Liberty, and was intended to mean that the group stood against "the oppression of all freedom".

name: FLASHE
bio: FLASHE debuted on July 4, 2012 under Flashe Entertainment. FLASHE (Hangul: 플래쉬) is a Korean Girlgroup under Flashe Entertainment. The group consists of 4 members: Narae, Seryeong, Yaerin and Sujin.

name: FLAVOR
bio: FLAVOR debuted on November 26, 2018 under FENT - FASCINO Entertainment. Flavor (Hangul: 플레이버) is a Sub-Unit of Upcoming Girlgroup Fanatics consisting of Doah, Chiayi and Yoonhye.

name: Fly To The Sky
bio: Fly To The Sky debuted on November 21, 1999 under H2 Media. KPOP duo composed of Korean-American Brian Joo and South Korean native Hwanhee. They were part of SM Entertainment until 2004.

name: Fromis_9
bio: Fromis_9 debuted on January 24, 2018 under Off The Record Entertainment. Fromis_9 (Hangul: 프로미스나인) is a South Korean Girlgroup formed through the 2017 reality show "Idol School".

name: FT ISLAND
kor_name: 에프티 아일랜드 エフティー・アイランド
bio: FT ISLAND debuted on June 7, 2007 under FNC Entertainment. First rock band created by FNC Entertainment. Composed of Choi Jong- hoon (leader, guitar, and keyboard), Lee Hong-gi (main vocals), Lee Jae-jin (bass and 2nd vocals), Song Seung-hyun (guitar, vocals, and rap), Choi Min-hwan and Seunghyun.

name: Gavy NJ
bio: Gavy NJ debuted on November 11, 2005 under Good Fellas Entertainment. Gavy NJ is a girl group that debuted under Good Fellas Entertainment.

name: GBB
bio: GBB debuted on May 1, 2018 under OGAM Entertainment. The group is made up of former SOL-T members and new members alike. They debuted on May 1st, 2018 with KEMI.

name: GFriend
bio: GFriend debuted on January 15, 2015 under Source Music. GFriend (Hangul: 여자친구; stylized as GFRIEND) is a six-member South Korean girl group formed by Source Music in 2015. The group consists of Sowon, Yerin, Eunha, Yuju, SinB, and Umji. They made their debut with the EP Season of Glass on January 16, 2015. GFriend won several 2015 female rookie awards and has garnered momentum since their debut, despite coming from a small company. In 2016, they continued their success with their third EP Snowflake and won first place on many music shows with the title song "Rough". They released their first full-length album LOL in July 2016.

name: Girl's Day
bio: Girl's Day debuted on July 7, 2010 under Dream Tea Entertainment. Girl's Day consists of 4 members. The girl group debuted in 2010, under Dream Tea Entertainment.

name: GIRLKIND
bio: GIRLKIND debuted on January 17, 2018 under Next Level Entertainment. GIRLKIND (걸카인드) is a 5 member girl group consisting of Medic Jin, JK, Xeheun, Sun J, and Ellyn. The group debuted January 17, 2018, under Next Level Entertainment with the song “FANCI”.

name: Girls' Generation
bio: Girls' Generation debuted on August 5, 2007 under S.M. Entertainment. Girls' Generation, also known as SNSD is a South Korean girl group formed by S.M. Entertainment. The group is composed of eight members: Taeyeon, Sunny, Tiffany, Hyoyeon, Yuri, Sooyoung, Yoona, and Seohyun. Originally a nine member group with Jessica, who later departed from the group in September 2014. Girls' Generation made their debut in 2007 with their album "Girls' Generation" in 2009 the groups popularity rose considerably after releasing their hit song "Gee" which was named one of the most popular songs in the 2000s by Melon

name: GIRLSGIRLS
bio: GIRLSGIRLS debuted on December 9, 2015 under H Brothers Entertainment. GIRLSGIRLS (여자여자) currently consists of 4 members: Bori, Rina, Aryoung, and Miso. The band debuted on December 09, 2015, under H Brothers Entertainment

name: GLAM
bio: GLAM debuted on July 16, 2012 under Big Hit Entertainment. Glam was a four (originally five) member girl group from South Korea. The group was formed by a collaboration between Big Hit Entertainment and Source Music. The group consisted of five members: Zinni, Trinity, Lee Jiyeon, Kim Dahee and Miso. The group's name is an acronym for GirLs be AMbitious.

name: Golden Child
bio: Golden Child debuted on August 28, 2017 under Woolim Entertainment. Golden Child (골든차일드) currently consists of 10 members: Daeyeol, Y, Jangjun, TAG, Seungmin, Jaehyun, Jibeom, Donghyun, Joochan, and Bomin. Golden Child debuted on August 28, 2017 with ‘DamDaDi', under Woolim Entertainment. On January 6, 2018, Woollim Entertainment announced Jaeseok left the group due to health issues.

name: Good Day
bio: Good Day debuted on August 31, 2017 under C9 Entertainment. GOOD DAY (굿데이) consists of 10 members. The band debuted in August 2017, under C9 Entertainment. Their debut track is 'Rolly'.

name: GOT7
bio: GOT7 debuted on January 16, 2014 under JYP Entertainment. GOT7 (갓세븐) is a seven-member boy group under JYP Entertainment. They debuted with "Girls Girls Girls" from their first mini-album Got It? on January 16, 2014. They are multinational with members from South Korea, Hong Kong, Thailand, and the United States.

name: GreatGuys
bio: GreatGuys debuted on July 25, 2017 under DNA Entertainment. GreatGuys (멋진녀석들) consists of 9 members: Jae I, Horyeong, Haneul, Daun, Donghwi, Dongin, Hwalchan, Uiyeon, Baekgyeol. Great Guys debuted on August 25, 2017, under DNA Entertainment.

name: Gugudan
bio: Gugudan debuted on June 28, 2016 under Jellyfish Entertainment. Gugudan (Hangul:구구단) is the first Girlgroup under Jellyfish Entertainment and consists of 9 members: Hana, Mimi, Haebin, Nayoung, Sejeong, Sally, Soyee, Mina and Hyeyeon. On October 25, 2018, Maknae Hyeyeon left the group in order to focus on her health and studies.

name: GWSN
bio: GWSN debuted on September 5, 2018 under Kiwi Pop. GWSN (Gongwon Sonyeo; 공원소녀) is a 7 member girl group under Kiwi Pop, a sublabel of Kiwi Media Group, consisting of Seoryoung, Seokyoung, Anne, Minju, SoSo, Miya, and Lena. The group consists of members who are from South Korea, Japan, and China.

name: H.B.Y
bio: H.B.Y debuted on August 16, 2017 under Rainbow Entertainment. H.B.Y., or Hot Blood Youth (열혈남아) is a 5 member boy group that debuted August 16, 2017 with the song Vroom Vroom/ Make it Ride. The member lineup consists of Taro, Marco, Bin, Kyuhyuk, and Jisan.

name: H.U.B
bio: H.U.B debuted on February 9, 2017 under Hope U Bounce. Before the group debuted Rui debuted on 2016 as a soloist with "Exiting". Originally H.U.B was conformed by four members, Keina, Gracie, Rui and Yeum . They released the pre-release single "Our Time Together" on November 24, 2016 later debuting on February 9, 2017 with "Girl Gang" also called "Girl in Black". It has no music video and was written and choreographed by the members. Later on May 31, 2017 was annunced that Hyosun (a contestant on Produce 101) was going to be added. A day later the released "Ooh Ooh" but Hyosun did not participate in it.

name: Halo
bio: Halo debuted on June 26, 2014 under Hi-Star Entertainment. Halo (헤일로) is a 6 member group form Hi-Star Entertainment. Members consist of: leader Ooon, vocalists Jayong, Heecheon, and Dino, and rappers Inhaeng and Yoondong. They debuted in 2014 with "Fever."

name: HashTag
bio: HashTag debuted on October 11, 2017 under L.U.K Factory. Hashtag (해시태그) consists of 7 members: Hyunji, Dajeong, Sua, Seungnin, Subin, Sojin and Aeji. They debuted on October 11, 2017 with the song “Hue”, under LUK Factory. They are produced by former Baby V.O.X member Kan Mi Youn.

name: Hello Venus
bio: Hello Venus debuted on June 6, 2012 under Fantagio. Hello Venus (헬로비너스) currently consists of 6 members: Alice, Nara, Lime, Seoyoung, Yooyoung, and Yeoreum. The band debuted on 2012, under Tricell Media (a joint between Pledis Entertainment and Fantagio). In 2014, it was announced that the company split and Hello Venus was to continue under Fantagio.

name: Hi Suhyun
bio: Hi Suhyun debuted on November 11, 2014 under YG Entertainment. Hi Suhyun consists of 2 members: Lee Hi & Lee Soohyun

name: High4
bio: . High4 (하이포) currently consists of three members: Alex, Myungho, and Youngjun. In February 2017, Sunggu announced he would be leaving the group. High4 debuted April 8, 2014 under N.A.P. Entertainment.

name: Highlight
bio: Highlight debuted on March 20, 2017 under Around Us Entertainment. Highlight was formerly known as Beast. The band consists of five members: Yoon Doo-joon, Yong Jun-hyung, Yang Yo-seob, Lee Gi-kwang, and Son Dong-woon. Original member Jang Hyun-seung officially left the group in April 2016. Later that year, the five remaining members moved labels from Cube Entertainment to Around Us Entertainment and subsequently changed their name to Highlight in 2017.

name: HISTORY
bio: HISTORY debuted on April 26, 2013 under Loen Entertainment. History was announced to be disbanded on May 12, 2017.

name: HONEYST
bio: HONEYST debuted on May 17, 2017 under FNC Entertainment.

name: HOTSHOT
bio: HOTSHOT debuted on October 31, 2014 under Star Crew Entertainment (formerly K.O Sound and Ardor & Able). Hotshot is a South Korean boy group formed by Star Crew Entertainment. They debuted on October 29, 2014, with their digital single "Take A Shot". The group consists of six-members: Junhyuk, Timoteo, Taehyun, Sungwoon, Yoonsan and Hojung.

name: Hyokuh
bio: Hyokuh debuted on September 18, 2014 under HIGHGRND.

name: iKON
bio: iKON debuted on September 15, 2015 under YG Entertainment. iKON is a South Korean boy band formed in 2015 by YG Entertainment. The group was first introduced in the reality survival program WIN: Who is Next as "Team B." After that, Team B went on to appear in the 2014 reality survival program Mix & Match, which determined the final seven-member line-up of iKON: B.I, Bobby, Jay, Ju-ne, Song, DK and Chan.

name: IM
bio: IM debuted on September 1, 2017 under Yama & Hotchicks. IM is a boygroup under Yama & Hotchicks Entertainment. Only 4 members have debuted as of 2017 and joined KBS' "The Unit". They are going to debut as a 10 member group.

name: Imfact
bio: Imfact debuted on January 27, 2016 under Star Empire Entertainment. Imfact (Hangul: 임팩트) is a South Korean Boygroup formed by Star Empire Entertainment in 2016. The group is composed of five members: Jian (Leader), Jeup, Taeho, Lee Sang and Ungjae.

name: IN2IT
bio: IN2IT debuted on October 26, 2017 under MMO Entertainment. IN2IT is a 7 member group under MMO Entertainment. This group was formed from the survival show BOYS24.

name: INFINITE
bio: INFINITE debuted on June 9, 2010 under Woollim Entertainment. Infinite (Korean: 인피니트; stylized as INFINITE) is a South Korean boy band formed in 2010 by Woollim Entertainment. The group is composed of six members: Sungkyu, Dongwoo, Woohyun, Sungyeol, L, and Sungjong. Originally a seven-piece group (with Hoya, who later departed from the group in August 2017)

name: Infinite F
bio: Infinite F debuted on December 2, 2014 under Woollim Entertainment. Infinite F (Korean: 인피니트F; stylized as INFINITE F) is the second sub-group of South Korean boy group Infinite formed by Woollim Entertainment in 2014. The sub-group consists of Infinite vocalists: Sungyeol, L and Sungjong. The sub-group made their simultaneous Japanese and Korean debuts with the single albums Koi no Sign and Azure.

name: INX
bio: INX debuted on August 2, 2016 under NA Entertainment.

name: IOI
bio: IOI debuted on May 4, 2016 under CJ E&M. IOI was a South Korean girl group formed by CJ E&M through the 2016 reality show Produce 101 on Mnet. The group was composed of eleven members chosen from a pool of 101 trainees from various entertainment companies.

name: IZ
bio: IZ debuted on August 31, 2017 under Music K Entertainment. IZ is a four-member band that debuted in August 31, 2017, under Music K Entertainment. The group is composed of Junyoung, Jihoo, Hyunjun, Woosu. In 2018, IZ won the New Hallyu Rookie Award in Soribada Best K-Music Awards

name: IZ*ONE
bio: IZ*ONE debuted on October 29, 2018 under Off The Record Entertainment. IZ*ONE (pronounced as "eyes one") is a twelve-member girl group formed through Mnet's competition reality show Produce 48. They are a temporary girl group who will be active for two and a half years on a special contract. The members are Eunbi (Leader), Sakura, Hyewon, Yena, Chaeyeon, Chaewon, Minju, Nako, Hitomi, Yuri, Yujin and Wonyoung (Center).

name: J2KC
bio: . J2KC (제이투케이씨) is a 5 member boy group from JSL Entertainment. The member lineup currently consists of Danny, Jerome, Jin, Min, and Jay.

name: JBJ
bio: JBJ debuted on October 18, 2017 under Just Be Joyful. JBJ consists of Takada Kenta, Jin Longguo, Kim Sang Gyun, Kim Dong Han, Noh Tae Hyun, Kim Tae Dong, and Kwon Hyun Bin. The group was put together by fans of Produce 101 Season 2, as they were the most popular trainees however they didn't get to debut as the final line up of '. Fave Entertainment will be managing them as they perform.

name: JBJ95
bio: JBJ95 debuted on October 30, 2018 under Star Road Entertainment. JBJ95 (JBJ coming from their roots and 95 because they were both born in '95) is a duo under Star Road Entertainment. The duo consists of Kenta and Sanggyun.

name: Jinusean
bio: Jinusean debuted on March 1, 1997 under YG Entertainment. South Korean hip hop duo composed of Jinu and Sean signed under YG Entertainment. They got famous for their track "Tell Me". Went on hiatus on 2004 but regained their fame through Infinity Challenge's TOTOGA and released an album on 2015

name: JJCC
bio: JJCC debuted on March 20, 2014 under Jackie Chan Group Korea. JJCC (제이제이씨씨) currently consists of 6 members. The band debuted on March 20, 2014, under the management of Jackie Chan Group Korea.

name: JYJ
bio: JYJ debuted on April 1, 2010 under Junsu, Yuchun, Jejung. JYJ (formerly known as Junsu/Yuchun/Jejung in Japan) is a South Korean pop group formed in 2010 by Jaejoong, Yoochun, and Junsu, the three former members of TVXQ. Their group name is taken from the initial letters of each member's names. The trio are managed by C-JeS Entertainment.

name: Kara
bio: Kara debuted on March 29, 2007 under DSP Entertainment. KARA was a South Korean pop girl group formed by DSP Media in 2007. The group's final lineup was composed of Park Gyuri, Han Seungyeon, Goo Hara and Heo Youngji. Members Nicole Jung and Kang Ji-young officially departed from the group in 2014, while Kim Sung-hee left in 2008. The group's name comes from the Greek word "chara" ( "joy"), which they interpreted to mean "sweet melody"

name: Kard
bio: Kard debuted on December 13, 2016 under DSP Entertainment. Kard (Hangul: 카드, also stylized as KARD, K.A.R.D or K♠RD) is a South Korean co-ed group formed by DSP Media in 2016. The group is composed of four members: J.seph, B.M, Somin and Jiwoo. They made their official debut on July 19, 2017 with the EP Hola Hola.

name: KHAN
bio: KHAN debuted on May 23, 2018 under Maroo Entertainment. KHAN (칸) is a South Korean duo, the duo consists of Minju and Euna Kim who both were former members of The Ark. They have shown attention-grabbing chemistry in the past before when they released ‘Goodbye Rain‘ before the official formation of KHAN. KHAN's debut song is "I'm Your Girl ?".

name: KNK
bio: KNK debuted on March 3, 2016 under 크나큰. KNK debuted as a five membered group under YNB Entertainment in March 2016, with members Kim Youjin, Park Seungjun, Jeong Inseong, Kim Jihun, and Oh Heejun. During late 2018, KNK departed from YNB Entertainment, and oldest member Kim Youjin left the group due to troubles with anxiety. It is said that KNK is currently working on starting their own agency, but as of right now their future is undetermined.

name: Laboum
bio: Laboum debuted on August 24, 2014 under NH Media and Nega Network. Laboum (라붐) currently consists of 5 members: Yujeong, Soyeon, ZN, Haein, and Solbin. They debuted on August 2014, under Global H Media (NH Media and Nega Network). On November 3 2017 it was announced that Yulhee left the band.

name: Ladies' Code
bio: Ladies' Code debuted on March 7, 2013 under Polaris Entertainment. Ladies' Code members are Ashley, known for her dance covers and singing on YouTube. Rise, former contestant of "Birth of A Great Star", So Jung who in turn was "Voice Korea" contestant, EunB and Zuny who were trainers of the company for a good time. They oficcially debuted on 2013 and are still active. Ladies Code was known for their funky sound but after two of the members passed away (EunB and Rise) they went on hiatus for two years and in their comeack in 2016 changed their style.

name: Laysha
bio: Laysha debuted on May 12, 2015 under JS Entertainment.

name: LedT
bio: . LedT was a three-member South Korean rock band formed by Starkim Entertainment in 2010, originally as LEDApple. The band's final lineup consisted of Seo Youngjun (JUN), Lee Kyumin (Kei) and Kim Hyoseok (AKi).

name: Like A Movie
bio: Like A Movie debuted on June 16, 2018 under Top Cloud Entertainment. Like A Movie (영화처럼) is a South Korean boy group under Top Cloud Entertainment.

name: LipBubble
bio: LipBubble debuted on March 22, 2017 under Zenith Media. LipBubble is a girl group under Zenith Media and debuted with "Popcorn" in 2017. Members consist of Ryua, Seoryn, Mirae, Haea, Eunbyeol, Ina and Hanbi.

name: Longguo&Shihyun
bio: Longguo&Shihyun debuted on July 31, 2017 under Choon Entertainment. The South Korean duo consists of Longguo and Shihyun. Both of them participated in Produce 101 Season 2.

name: LOONA
bio: LOONA debuted on August 20, 2018 under Blockberry Creative. LOONA consists of 12 members: HeeJin, HyunJin, HaSeul, YeoJin, ViVi, Kim Lip, JinSoul, Choerry, Yves, Chuu, Go Won and Olivia Hye. Each month, from October 2016 to late 2018, a new member or sub-unit was revealed through the release of a single album or extended play, introducing them to the group. In 2018, with the project completed, all twelve members debuted as one group on August 20th with the title song "Hi High".

name: Lovelyz
bio: Lovelyz debuted on November 17, 2014 under Woollim Entertainment. Lovelyz is a South Korean girl group formed in 2014 by Woollim Entertainment and its company first girl group. The group consists of eight members: Baby Soul, Jiae, Jisoo, Mijoo, Kei, Jin, Sujeong and Yein.

name: M.Fect
bio: M.Fect debuted on April 27, 2015 under Midas Entertainment.

name: M.I.B
bio: . M.I.B (Hangul: 엠아이비; known as Most Incredible Busters) was a South Korean hip hop quartet from Jungle Entertainment. Jungle Entertainment reported that 1.7 million USD was invested for the group's debut album since 2009. The album was personally produced and four tracks were part of a solo spin-off to show that each member can stand on their own. Their self-titled album, Most Incredible Busters was released on October 25.[

name: MADTOWN
bio: MADTOWN debuted on October 6, 2014 under GNI Entertainment. Madtown was a South Korean boy group formed in 2014 by J. Tune Camp. The group consisted of Moos, Daewon, Lee Geon, Jota, Heo Jun, Buffy and H.O. Their debut album, Mad Town, was released on October 6, 2014. Two of the members, Moos and Buffy, originally debuted as the hip hop duo Pro C in 2013. Starting December 22, 2016, Madtown's contract was sold to GNI Entertainment after J. Tune Camp closed. On The Unit, Daewon and Lee Geon confirmed Madtown's disbandment.

name: Mamamoo
bio: Mamamoo debuted on June 18, 2014 under Rainbow Bridge World. MAMAMOO (마마무) consist of 4 members: Solar, Moonbyul, Wheein and Hwasa. MAMAMOO deuted in 2014, under Rainbow Bridge World (formerly WA Entertainment).

name: MAP6
bio: MAP6 debuted on November 10, 2015 under Dream T Entertainment. MAP6 is a 5 member boy group from Dream T Entertainment consisting of members: Minhyuk, J.Jun, Sign, Sun, and J.Vin. They debuted on November 10th, 2015 with the single "Storm." Their fandom name is Mapsi.

name: Marmello
bio: Marmello debuted on May 24, 2017 under Rolling CultureOne. MARMELLO (마르멜로) is a 4-member South Korean girl band under Rolling CultureOne. The band is composed of 5 members: Youna, Doeun, Gaeun, and Hyeona. MARMELLO officially debuted on May 24, 2017. Before debut, they have been doing several gigs and concerts. All of the members have been friends since high school.

name: MAS
bio: MAS debuted on August 1, 2016 under RBW Entertainment. MAS (Formally M.A.S 0094) is a band of childhood neighbours under RBW Entertainment. Members consist of Yonghoon, Harin, Kanghyun, Dongmyeong, and Cya. They debuted in 2016 with "Feel Good". They are currently (October 2017) taking part in KBS' idol rebooting survival show "The Unit"

name: MASC
bio: MASC debuted on August 18, 2016 under JJ Holic Media.

name: Matilda
bio: Matilda debuted on March 17, 2016 under Box Media Entertainment. MaTilDa is a South Korean girl group from agency BOXMEDIA. Consists of four members such as Haena, DanA, Semmi, Saebyeol They debuted with the single “Macarena” on March 17th, 2016

name: Maywish
bio: Maywish debuted on October 17, 2018 under 307Studio. Maywish is a South Korean Girlgroup formed by 307 Studio. The group is composed of 4 members: Anna, Soeun, Jelly and Hyoin.

name: MBLAQ
bio: MBLAQ debuted on October 15, 2009 under J. Tune Camp. MBLAQ (Korean: 엠블랙, Japanese: エムブラック; an acronym for Music Boys Live in Absolute Quality) is a South Korean boy group created by South Korean entertainer Rain under J. Tune Camp. The group consists of Seungho, G.O, and Mir, and formerly Lee Joon and Thunder. The group debuted on October 15, 2009, at Rain's Legend of Rainism concert. On October 14, 2009, the group released their debut single album, Just BLAQ, which topped various online and offline music charts in South Korea. The group then released their first extended play album Y on May 19, 2010, and on January 10, 2011, MBLAQ released their first studio album, BLAQ Style. On December 16, 2014, it was announced Joon and Thunder had departed from the group and they will focus on individual activities for the time being.

name: Melody day
bio: Melody day debuted on February 25, 2014 under Cre.Ker Entertainment. Melody Day (멜로디데이) is a 4-member girl group under Cre.Ker Entertainment. The group consists of Yeoeun, Yoomin, Yein, and Chahee. Melody Day debuted on February 25, 2014.

name: Mind U
bio: Mind U debuted on October 25, 2013 under Starship Entertainment. Mind U, formerly known as Acourve, is a South Korean duo formed by Bridge Media in 2013. They debuted on October 25, 2013, with "What I Want To Say", then later re-debuted under Starship Entertainment on April 27, 2017, with "Loved U".

name: Miss A
bio: Miss A debuted on July 1, 2010 under JYP Entertainment. Miss A was a South Korean girl group based in South Korea formed by JYP Entertainment in 2010. Their group name stands for Miss Asia and the highest rank, A. The group was composed of four total members, Fei, Jia, Min, and Suzy. In May 2016, Jia ended her contract with JYP Entertainment and left the group. Miss A's final album release was titled "Colors," which was released in March 2015.

name: Momoland
bio: Momoland debuted on November 10, 2016 under MLD Entertainment. MOMOLAND (모모랜드) consist of 9 members: Hyebin, Yeonwoo, Jane, Taeha, Nayun, Daisy, JooE, Ahin and Nancy. The band debuted on November 10, 2016, under MLD Entertainment.

name: Monsta X
bio: Monsta X debuted on May 14, 2015 under Starship Entertainment. Monsta X are a 7 member group under the label Starship Entertainment. The members were chosen through a survival show hold between the label and Mnet. Their name, unlike most people think, is not referring to "monster" but to the french expression " Mon Sta" which translates into "my star" in english. X stands for the infinite possibilities as the variable character in equations. The fandom is called Monbebe which also translates do "my baby" from french. Their debut song is called Trespass.

name: MVP
bio: MVP debuted on March 13, 2017 under PH Entertainment.

name: MXM
bio: MXM debuted on July 27, 2017 under Brand New Music. MXM is a South Korean duo under Brand New Music that consists of Brand New Boys members, Im Young-min and Kim Dong-hyun. Im Young-min and Kim Dong-hyun met when they signed with Brand New Music as trainees. They participated in the second season of the survival reality show Produce 101 with two other trainees, Park Woo-jin and Lee Dae-hwi, to represent their agency. name: N.Sonic
bio: N.Sonic debuted on October 6, 2011 under C2K Entertainment. N.Sonic (엔소닉) is a 6 member boy group from C2K Entertainment. The current member lineup consists of J.Heart, Sihoo, Byul, Minkee, Bongjun, and Zion. The group is currently on hiatus as they have filed a lawsuit against C2K Entertainment.

name: N.Tic
bio: N.Tic debuted on February 26, 2018 under Yechan Media. N.TIC (엔티크), also known as New Trend Icon, is a South Korean boy group under Yechan Entertainment (formerly JJ Entertainment). They were also formerly known as J-Peace and New-Ace.

name: Nasty Nasty
bio: Nasty Nasty debuted on September 3, 2014 under Star Empire Entertainment. Nasty Nasty (네스티네스티) is a collaboration unit between Nine Muses and Ze:a. They debuted in 2014 with the song Knock. The lineup consists of Ze:A's Kevin and Nine Muses' Kyungri and Sojin.

name: NATURE
bio: NATURE debuted on August 3, 2018 under CH Entertainment. Nature is 9 member girl group under n.CH Entertainment set to debut in August 3th in 2018 The 9-piece act is multinational, consisting of members from Korea, Japan and China. It is the first band to be launched by n.CH Entertainment.

name: NCT
bio: NCT debuted on April 4, 2016 under SM Entertainment. NCT (엔시티) is a South Korean boy group formed by S.M. Entertainment.Their name stands for the Hallyu localization project Neo Culture Technology, a term coined by S.M. Entertainment founder Lee Soo-man to describe the group's concept of having an unlimited number of members divided into multiple sub-units based in various cities worldwide.

name: NCT 127
bio: NCT 127 debuted on July 10, 2016 under S.M. Entertainment. NCT 127 is the seoul-based sub-unit of SM Entertainment's boy group, NCT. The unit debuted on July 7, 2016, with their first extended play NCT #127, with the members: leader Taeyong, Mark, Yuta, Taeil, Winwin, Jaehyun, and Haechan. Later on, members: Doyoung, Johnny, and Jungwoo were also added.

name: NCT Dream
bio: NCT Dream debuted on August 24, 2016 under S.M. Entertainment. All the members of NCT except for Renjun and Chenle were formerly part of SM Rookies, a pre-debut group of S.M. Entertainment trainees. In January 2016, S.M. Entertainment founder Lee Soo- man gave a presentation at the SM Coex Artium titled "SMTOWN: New Culture Technology 2016", speaking about the agency's plans for a new boy group in line with their "culture contents" strategy that would be debuting different teams based in different countries around the world. On August 18, S.M. Entertainment announced that NCT's third unit would be called NCT Dream and will be composed of teenagers. Their first single "Chewing Gum" was released on August 24 and the unit had their debut stage on M Countdown on August 25. The unit consists of seven members: Mark, Renjun, Jeno, Haechan, Jaemin, Chenle, and Jisung.

name: NCT U
bio: NCT U debuted on April 9, 2016 under SM Entertainment. NCT (Hangul: 엔시티) is a South Korean boy group formed by S.M. Entertainment. Their name stands for the Hallyu localization project Neo Culture Technology, a term coined by S.M. Entertainment founder Lee Soo- man to describe the group's concept of having an unlimited number of members divided into multiple sub- units based in various cities worldwide. NCT's first sub-unit, NCT U, made its debut in April 2016 with digital singles "The 7th Sense", and "Without You." The group has no permanent members and will rotate between anyone from NCT.

name: NeonPunch
bio: NeonPunch debuted on June 1, 2018 under A100 Entertainment. NEON PUNCH (네온펀치) is the first girl group from A100 Ent who will debut in June 2018. In March 2017, A100 announced that they would be doing a girl group project and a boy group project. After that A100 Ent started posting covers on their YouTube of their girl group. While they did the covers they were always masked and their identities secret. But they recently revealed their identities.

name: Nine Muses
bio: Nine Muses debuted on August 12, 2010 under Star Empire Entertainment. Nine Muses (Hangul: 나인뮤지스), also known as 9Muses, is a four-member South Korean Girlgroup formed by Star Empire Entertainment. They debuted on August 12th, 2010 with the song "No Playboy" from their first single album "Let's Have a Party."

name: NTB
bio: NTB debuted on May 28, 2018 under One World Entertainment.

name: S.E.S
bio: . S.E.S. (Hangul: 에스.이.에스; initialism for Sea, Eugene, Shoo) is a South Korean girl group trio formed by S.M. Entertainment in 1997, consisting of members Bada, Eugene, and Shoo. In their early years, they were also known as the female counterpart of H.O.T., and raised phenomenal popularity at the time.[citation needed] S.E.S. is considered one of K-pop's first highly successful girl groups. They were challenged by groups like Fin.K.L and Baby V.O.X, which debuted soon after S.E.S. and also enjoyed success. The group officially disbanded in December 2002 after Bada's and Eugene's contracts expired, though Shoo eventually also parted ways with S.M. Entertainment in 2006. Their final release was the compilation album Beautiful Songs released in mid-2003, where they last promoted their last original single "S.II.S (Soul To Soul)", from the greatest hits album Friend.

Their biggest hits include "So Cool", "Alone", "Touch My Body", "Loving U" and "Give It to Me".

bio: . SS501 is a South Korean boy group formed under the management of DSP Media,[1] formerly known as Daesung Entertainment and DSP Entertainment.[2] The group debuted on June 8, 2005 with five members: Kim Hyun-joong, Heo Young-saeng, Kim Kyu-jong, Park Jung-min and Kim Hyung-jun,[3] along with their debut mini-album entitled Warning.[4] They achieved their first number one song with "Never Again" (2005) and released their first studio album, S.T 01 Now in 2006.

Entertainment, the group comprised a total of thirteen members at its peak. Super Junior originally debuted with twelve members.

bio: . VERIVERY is a pre-debut group from Jellyfish Entertainment, home to VIXX & Gugudan. Their name is an acronym for various, energetic, real and innovation (VERI). They are skilled in music, performance, visuals, producing and creative skills. They want "creative idol" to come to people's mind after watching their reality program "NOW VERIVERY" which concluded on November 9th.

name: Vermuda
bio: Vermuda debuted on June 13, 2017 under Pacemaker Entertainment. Vermuda (버뮤다), previously known as Beam, is a 5-member boy group under Triple J (JJJ) Entertainment. The group consists of U, Choiseon, Nakang, Jun, and Je1. Vermuda debuted on June 13, 2017 with the song "Dream Girl". Their fandom name was announced to be Triangle.

name: Vibe
bio: Vibe debuted on February 1, 2002 under Major9. Vibe is a South Korean R&B duo under Major9. They originally debuted as a trio of two male singers and a rapper.

name: VICTON
bio: VICTON debuted on November 9, 2016 under Plan A Entertainment. Victon is a boygroup under Plan A Entertainment. They debuted in 2016 with the track "I'm Fine". They are the little brother group of APINK.

name: VIXX
bio: VIXX debuted on May 24, 2012 under Jellyfish Entertainment. VIXX is a six-member South Korean boy band, formed by Jellyfish Entertainment in 2012. VIXX consists of N, Leo, Ken, Ravi, Hongbin and Hyuk. They are also known as concept idols.

name: VIXX LR
bio: VIXX LR debuted on August 17, 2015 under Jellyfish Entertainment. Composed of members Leo and Ravi, VIXX LR is the very first sub unit of concept-dols VIXX.

name: Voisper
bio: Voisper debuted on March 2, 2016 under Evermore Music. Voisper auditioned on Superstar K6 in 2014 as a group called North Incheon Nineteen, and later signed with Evermore Music in January of the following year. The group's name is a play on the words "voice' + "whisper", patterned after the group released its first mini-album Voice + Whisper in November 2016.

name: Vromance
bio: Vromance debuted on July 12, 2016 under RBW Entertainment (Rainbow Bridge World). Vromance (브로맨스) is a 4-member South Korean boy group under RBW Entertainment (Rainbow Bridge World). The group consists of Janghyun, Hyunkyu, Chandong, and Hyunseok. Vromance debuted on July 12, 2016.

name: VX
bio: VX debuted on July 13, 2015 under JJ Entertainment. VX is a 5 member group from JJ Entertainment that debuted with the song "Fantasy." Their member lineup includes Jinhwa, Siyoon, JT, Jeki, and La-e. Their official fandom name is Sunshine.

name: W24
bio: W24 debuted on February 25, 2018 under JARMY Entertainment. W24, also known as World 24 Hours(더블유24), is a South Korean boy group under JARMY Entertainment.

name: Wanna One
bio: Wanna One debuted on August 7, 2017 under Wanna One. Wanna One (Hangul: 워너원, stylized as WANNA·ONE) is a South Korean boy band formed by CJ E&M through the 2017 series Produce 101 Season 2. The group is composed of 11 members: Kang Daniel, Park Ji-hoon, Lee Dae-hwi, Kim Jae-hwan, Ong Seong-wu, Park Woo-jin, Lai Kuan-lin, Yoon Ji-sung, Hwang Min-hyun, Bae Jin-young and Ha Sung-woon. The group debuted on August 7, 2017 and will be promoting until December 31, 2018 under YMC Entertainment and CJ E&M.

name: WeAreYoung
bio: WeAreYoung debuted on February 21, 2017 under MyMusic. WeAreYoung is a South Korean duo under MyMusic Entertainment.

name: Weki Meki
bio: Weki Meki debuted on August 8, 2017 under Fantagio. Weki Meki (Hangul: 위키미키) is a South Korean girl group formed by Fantagio in 2017. The group consists of eight members: Ji Suyeon, Elly, Choi Yoojung, Kim Doyeon, Sei, Lua, Rina, and Lucy.

name: Winner
bio: Winner debuted on August 17, 2014 under YG Entertainment. Winner is a South Korean boy group from YG Entertainment. It is consist of 4 members named Kang Seungyoon, Kim Jinwoo, Song Mino and Lee Seunghoon. They became popular through a survival show "WIN: Who is Next" as Team A in which they had to fight their way to the top versus Team B which is now called IKON. They are originally five members but Nam Taehyun, the group's former member/maknae, had to leave because of personal reasons on November 2016. These boys paved their way to the industry by releasing songs full of R&B and alternative pop songs that will pierce your heart because of its sentimentality and deep lyrics. Now, they are active with their world tour named 2018 WINNER EVERYWHERE TOUR and Song Mino, the group's rapper, will be releasing his first solo album named 'XX' this November 26th.

name: Wonder Girls
bio: Wonder Girls debuted on February 13, 2007 under JYP Entertainment. Wonder Girls was a South Korean girl group and band formed by producer Park Jin-young under JYP Entertainment in 2006, which debuted in 2007. The group's final line-up consisted of Yubin, Yeeun, Sunmi and Hyerim. Members Sunye and Sohee officially left the group in 2015, while Hyuna left in late 2007.

name: XENO-T
bio: XENO-T debuted on February 21, 2018 under HUNUS Entertainment. Formerly known as Topp Dogg (탑독), the group rebranded as XENO-T (제노티) with its 5 remaining members: Sangdo, Hojoon, B-Joo, Xero and Sangwon on February 21st of 2018.

name: YDPP
bio: YDPP debuted on April 5, 2018 under Brand New Music & Starship Entertainment.

name: ZE:A
bio: ZE:A debuted on January 7, 2010 under Star Empire Entertainment. ZE:A (제국의 아이들) consists of 9 members. The band debuted on January 7, 2010, under Star Empire Entertainment. They disbanded January 6th, 2017,

name: Zetta
bio: Zetta debuted on July 15, 2016 under KN Entertainment. Zetta is a 5 member boy group from KN Entertainment. The member lineup currently consists of B.Top, Zero, Hojun, Neo, and Daon. Member Sunghyun left earlier due to personal reasons.
